§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Suppose $𝒳$ is a finite set. ⦉

  ‖ A distribution $p: 𝒳 → [0,1]$ is a ❬normalized exponential
    distribution❭ (also ❬Gibbs distribution❭, ❬Boltzmann
    distribution❭) if there exists a function $F: 𝒳 → 𝗥$ so
    that
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ p(x) = \frac{\exp(-F(x))}{∑_{ξ ∈ 𝒳} \exp(-F(ξ))} \quad
        \text{for all } x ∈ 𝒳 ⦉
    ⦉⦉

  ‖ The function $F$ is sometimes called the ❬energy❭ (or
    ❬energy function❭) of $p$. ⦉
